# ROI Command Vocabulary (Codex AGENTS.md snippet)

Append the contents of this file to your `~/.codex/AGENTS.md` (or to
`<project>/.codex/AGENTS.md` for project-scoped vocabulary).

---

## ROI commands

ROI is a skill-driven lifecycle. Each `roi:*` command opens a SKILL.md
under `<roi-checkout>/skills/` and follows its procedure. Skills shell to
`node <roi-checkout>/scripts/lifecycle.mjs <verb> '<json>'` to persist
state in SQLite.

| Command | Stage | Skill |
|---|---|---|
| `roi:start [goal]` | Open mission | `skills/roi-start/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:clarify` | Refine brief | `skills/roi-clarify/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:source` | Record research | `skills/roi-source/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:outline` | Generate plans | `skills/roi-outline/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:go` | Implement plans | `skills/roi-go/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:draft` / `roi:run` | Open / resume run | `skills/roi-draft/SKILL.md`, `skills/roi-run/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:drive` | Lifecycle orchestrator (pauses at gates) | `skills/roi-drive/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:verify` / `roi:review` | Record verdict | `skills/roi-verify/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:edit` | Respond to non-pass | `skills/roi-edit/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:publish` | Record publication | `skills/roi-publish/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:learn` / `roi:enlighten` | Pattern detection | `skills/roi-learn/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:inspect` / `roi:status` | Read state | `skills/roi-inspect/SKILL.md` |
| `roi:cancel` | Cancel run | `skills/roi-cancel/SKILL.md` |

The helper's canonical verb surface:

```bash
node <roi-checkout>/scripts/lifecycle.mjs --list-verbs
```

`roi:drive` is a thin orchestrator. It reads `next_actions` from the
helper and opens the corresponding stage skill. **Mandatory pauses** at
`verify_gate` and `publish_gate` — the operator runs `roi:verify` and
`roi:publish` explicitly.

Each skill closes with a standard Reporting block surfacing
`next_actions` verbatim plus one bridge sentence. Do not invent next
actions; the helper is the authority.

Storage: `<roi-checkout>/.data/roi.sqlite` (override with
`ROI_SQLITE_PATH`).
